				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Here is a cut and past of the post.
<br />

<br />

<br />
"I am using this simple method to max my melee skills right now at lvl 51. Seriously, right now I am watching myself effortlessly raise my piercing skill. To the best of my knowledge, this is not an exploit, but use at your own risk anyhow because SOE has some weird ideas sometimes. 
<br />

<br />
Here's what you do: 
<br />
Go to Paineel and bring some fast, low damage weapons (and a KEI wouldn't hurt just for the extra wis). Take a left from zone in (don't fall down the Hole), go past the guards, and into the little area in front of the Warrens zone. There you should see an erudite named Erandi Natasu. He is about lvl 40 or so and is a shadow knight. The beauty of this is that he has plenty of hps, but his max melee hit is 19. Thats right, he hits for up to 19 damage! And he is dark blue con at lvl 51. The most hurt he will do to you is his 400 dmg harm touch. Other than that you can just slow him and beat him senseless. He gives no faction hits or loot, but is worth about 1% AA. Respawn is about 8mins or so. 
<br />

<br />
I'll leave you to your own devices, but what i like to do is this. Summon lvl 15 warder and dont' buff it. Then when the erudite spawns, I send in the pet to eat the HT. This kills the pet and leaves me with a pansy erudite all to myself. I then proceed to melee him down with low dmg, low dly weapons and heal myself / re-slow as needed. When he hits 20% he'll run, so I snare him with my sargasso spear and swap back to crappy(er) weapons. My goal is just skill ups so I use the lowest damage and delay weapons i can find to keep him alive longer, but do what you want."<br />_________________<br />Karana Half Elf Ranger of the 48th Season
<br />

<br />
Soullbash
<br />
54th Level Beastlord
<br />

<br />
The Rathe</span><span class="gentblsmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
