I see...but massive <span style="text-decoration: underline">under</span>-cons is "just part of the game"?
<br />

<br />
We deal with under-cons all the time. I don't see why the when we find something that is an over-con that we should consider it an exploit and leave it alone by taking any moral high ground. The mob can hit back. He's not perma-rooted. Heck, he can HT. If this mob were unbalancing the game, then SOE would change it.
<br />

<br />
I'm level 42, and I'm having my doubts that <span style="font-style: italic">I</span> can take him based on what Xhad is saying.
